Doctor.com ProfilePoints™


ProfilePoints™ measure the overall completeness of a
        provider's profile, including items like having a photo, a biography,
        insurance, payment options, etc. A full breakdown of points can be seen
        by providers with Doctor.com accounts when editing their profile on Doctor.com.
        
By showing providers with higher ProfilePoints™ first,
        we make it easier for you to quickly identify the most informative profiles on Doctor.com
        







Find Philadelphia, PA Doctors

        Go to Provider Search
    













Use the links below to start your search
﻿Philadelphia’s leadership in medicine dates back to at least the time of its famous resident Benjamin Franklin, whose 18th-century writings at the National Library of Medicine reflect his interests in medical science: lead poisoning, smallpox, even the invention of medical devices.

Today, the city remains at the forefront of medical care and innovation, and is home to biomedical research and pharmaceutical companies like GlaxoSmithKline. The Philadelphia region is recognized for premier hospitals that include Temple University and Thomas Jefferson University Hospital.

Hospital of the University of Pennsylvania offers nationally recognized specialty care in cancer, diabetes treatment, and ophthalmology – among other specialties ranked by U.S. News and World Report. The Children’s Hospital of Philadelphia was the first hospital in the nation dedicated to children’s health care, and this 535-bed facility remains second-to-none in a range of pediatric specialties. 

Popular and widely accepted insurance plans include Aetna, Blue Cross Blue Shield and Cigna.  















